Effect sizes were labelled following Cohen's
(1988) recommendations.

The Welch Two Sample t-test testing the
difference between mg2$control and mg2$Mg2
(mean of x = 15.68, mean of y = 10.52)
suggests that the effect is positive,
statistically significant, and large
(difference = 5.16, 95% CI [3.83, 6.49],
t(17.35) = 8.15, p < .001; Cohen's d = 3.65,
95% CI [2.14, 5.12])
